race.comment: SQUAZEEMOTO (10) is a tough one to get a line on with King Island form dominating his form card, but the one run here was last start when he was only beaten 2-1/4 lengths by Tookay Pete, who won at Sandown on Wed. It's doubtful many of his rivals here could have done likewise, so he deserves another chance. ROWDY ANTHEM (1) turned in a modest performance when a 4-1/2-length 10th last time at Kyneton but was a winner the start prior and had form before that you'd expect to measure up here. MR TIME (8) turned in a much better effort last time out to score by a nose over 1000m at Healesville and while that might be picnic form, he was only beaten a length here in 0-62 grade on Dec 29. MISS HIMALAYA (11) is drawn to take advantage of a drop back in trip.
